<paragraph id="FF60925385D28EAD45261EC8B9808753" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">
<taxonomicName id="88F264D37D28D9B0BD2200AE1A0E1418" authorityName="L. Wu, Y. F. Huang &amp; Z. J. Wen" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Spiradiclis detianensis" order="Gentianales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="detianensis">
<emphasis id="0E068949943622E40778F895DB039C5E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Spiradiclis detianensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="2C9565F2ADD02E618EDB36400ACB803F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. spathulata" order="Gentianales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spathulata">
<emphasis id="426B6CE2B09140EE2862F4D5112EF97D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">S. spathulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in morphology, since both have subrosetted habit, obovate-oblanceolate leaf blades, long peduncles and subglobose capsules, but it differs mainly by its corolla tubular-funnel shaped (vs. slenderly salver shaped), 4.5-6.8 (vs. 1.5-2) mm in diam. at the middle and densely pubescence inside corolla near base and densely puberulent above anther and onto lobes (vs. glabrous except a ring of long hairs at the middle) (more detailed comparisons are listed in Table 
<tableCitation id="B50F4D1C49D374BF6000FB6EEEC03593" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Morphological comparison of Spiradiclis detianensis, S. tubiflora and S. cordata Lo et W. L. Sha." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/209FDFFD650FB6EEC026753B18293B73" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" tableUuid="209FDFFD650FB6EEC026753B18293B73">1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7E9BE18B5858B9DA80C7C158F4EC02CE" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">
<taxonomicName id="A2C182C4263719786FDF91645ECB5D78" authorityName="L. Wu, Y. F. Huang &amp; Z. J. Wen" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Spiradiclis detianensis" order="Gentianales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="detianensis">
<emphasis id="C97A0AC839CA40DC02ECCE29F8179336" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Spiradiclis detianensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a distinct species in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="D1DBD42F9518830B31039677DE87BBED" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Spiradiclis" order="Gentianales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="53205F68F627CBAC4715B56820B7CE32" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Spiradiclis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to the corolla tubes 18-22 mm long and having the shape of a reversed wine bottle, with an abruptly narrowed lower third, 4.5-6.8 mm in diam. at throat, 1.8-2.5 mm in diam. near base. Until now, only one other known species, 
<taxonomicName id="E0530F7F5769965D702CF64BFA716F5B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. tubiflora" order="Gentianales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tubiflora">
<emphasis id="046AA0322035597C0F6D60E1E49488FA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">S. tubiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.Wu, B.M.Wang &amp; B.Pan (
<bibRefCitation id="C13BB2076D0D22079C1E56557C7572A6" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.130.34625" author="Wu, L" journalOrPublisher="PhytoKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" pagination="217 - 224" refId="B24" refString="Wu, L, Wang, BM, Pan, B, Yu, XL, 2019b. Spiradiclis tubiflora (Rubiaceae), a new cave-dwelling species from southern China. PhytoKeys 130: 217 - 224, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.130.34625" title="Spiradiclis tubiflora (Rubiaceae), a new cave-dwelling species from southern China." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.130.34625" volume="130" year="2019 b">Wu et al. 2019b</bibRefCitation>
), has a similar corolla shape (see Fig. 
<figureCitation id="91C745EEB1722D7A06BD36936488C5C4" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Spiradiclis detianensis A habit B inflorescence C leaves D, E stipule F, G short- and long-styled flower, front view H opened long- and short-styled flower, showing style and stamens I ovary, side view J infructescence, side view. S. tubiflora K habit L inflorescence. Scale bars: 1 cm (B, C, H, J, L); 2 mm (D, E, F, G, I). Photos by Z. J. Wen and L. Wu." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.184.69886.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/606623" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">2 K &amp; L</figureCitation>
). However, 
<taxonomicName id="A7DA07E9838F2AA4EC445C8789912AB6" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. detianensis" order="Gentianales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="detianensis">
<emphasis id="99F18CD05574AA471CA975AB0372F8EF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">S. detianensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="1E12D7632F8A6ACDCD05CE528BCE933F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. tubiflora" order="Gentianales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tubiflora">
<emphasis id="2091ED97A5410DAAA12C12AFA22195E4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">S. tubiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
principally by its rosulate habit (vs. procumbent to creeping), leaf blades longer than 7 cm and wider than 2 cm (vs. shorter than 2.5 cm and narrower than 1.5 cm), secondary veins 7-10 pairs (vs. 3-5 pairs) and longer corolla tubes (vs. 18-22 mm vs. 14-16 mm) (more detailed comparisons are listed in Table 
<tableCitation id="8BFBCCEFA0511B752684B067F34C80AE" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Morphological comparison of Spiradiclis detianensis, S. tubiflora and S. cordata Lo et W. L. Sha." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/209FDFFD650FB6EEC026753B18293B73" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" tableUuid="209FDFFD650FB6EEC026753B18293B73">1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
